61. The Comificius to whom Catullus addressed the pathetic appeal oi c. 38 was a poet (ci. vv. 7 and 8), and is doubtless to be identified with the Cornificius mentioned by Ovid (Trist. II. 436) in connection with other verse-writers of the period ol Catullus. It is not so clear, though quite possible, that he is the Q. Cornificius to whom Cicero wrote friendly letters (Fam. XII. 17-30), dated between 45 and 43 nc. Sextius, the general oi the second triumvirate.
